<!--
    Test Case: Multi-Level Visit Hierarchy
    Scenario: Demonstrates complex nested visit relationships
        
    1. SIMPLE 2-LEVEL HIERARCHY (Encounters 1-3):
       - Encounter 1: 30-day Inpatient admission (LAYER 1 - Parent)
         └─ Encounter 2: 10-day ICU stay (LAYER 2 - Nested child)
         └─ Encounter 3: 1-day Procedure (LAYER 2 - Nested child)

    2. SIMPLE 3-LEVEL HIERARCHY (Encounters 4-6):
       - Encounter 4: 20-day Inpatient (LAYER 1 - Longer parent)
         └─ Encounter 5: 5-day Inpatient (LAYER 2 - Shorter parent, Nested child of Layer 1)
            └─ Encounter 6: 1-day Procedure (LAYER 3 - Nested child of Layer 2)

    3. COMPLEX 3-LEVEL HIERARCHY (Encounters 7-10):
       - Encounter 7: 30-day Inpatient admission (LAYER 1 - Top parent)
         └─ Encounter 8: 10-day ICU stay (LAYER 2 - Mid-level parent)
            └─ Encounter 9: 1-day Procedure in ICU (LAYER 3 - Nested child of Layer 2)
         └─ Encounter 10: 2-day Emergency procedure (LAYER 2 - Nested child of Layer 1)

    4. NON-QUALIFYING PARENT (Encounter 11-12):
       - Encounter 11: 400-day Inpatient (TOO LONG - exceeds 365 day threshold, should remain in visit_occurrence)
         └─ Encounter 12: 2-day procedure (NO VALID PARENT - should remain in visit_occurrence)

    5. AMBIGUOUS PARENTS AT DIFFERENT HIERARCHY LEVELS (Encounters 13-17):
       - Encounter 13: 15-day Inpatient (Nov 1-15, LAYER 1)
         └─ Encounter 14: 4-day Inpatient (Nov 10-13, LAYER 2 nested in Encounter 13)
            └─ Encounter 16: 1-day (Nov 10, LAYER 3 nested in Encounter 14)
       - Encounter 15: 10-day Inpatient (Nov 11-20, LAYER 1, NOT in Encounter 13)
       - Encounter 17: 1-day (Nov 12, AMBIGUOUS - has parents Encounter 13, 14, and 15)
         Parents Encounter 13 and Encounter 14 are hierarchical chain, but Encounter 15 is sibling to Encounter 13
         → Encounter 17 stays in visit_occurrence due to ambiguity

    Expected Output:
    visit_occurrence table:
    - Encounter 1 (30-day IPD, parent of 2 & 3)
    - Encounter 4 (20-day IPD, parent of 5)
    - Encounter 7 (30-day IPD, parent of 8 & 10)
    - Encounter 11 (400-day IPD, too long to be parent)
    - Encounter 12 (2-day procedure, no valid parent)
    - Encounter 13 (15-day IPD, parent of Encounter 14)
    - Encounter 15 (10-day IPD, standalone)
    - Encounter 17 (1-day, ambiguous parents)
    
    visit_detail table:
    - Encounter 2 (10-day ICU, visit_occurrence_id=Enc1, visit_detail_parent_id=NULL)
    - Encounter 3 (1-day Proc, visit_occurrence_id=Enc1, visit_detail_parent_id=NULL)
    - Encounter 5 (5-day IPD, visit_occurrence_id=Enc4, visit_detail_parent_id=NULL)
    - Encounter 6 (1-day Proc, visit_occurrence_id=Enc4, visit_detail_parent_id=Enc5)
    - Encounter 8 (10-day ICU, visit_occurrence_id=Enc7, visit_detail_parent_id=NULL)
    - Encounter 9 (1-day Proc, visit_occurrence_id=Enc7, visit_detail_parent_id=Enc8)
    - Encounter 10 (2-day Emg, visit_occurrence_id=Enc7, visit_detail_parent_id=NULL)
    - Encounter 14 (4-day IPD, visit_occurrence_id=Enc13, visit_detail_parent_id=NULL)
    - Encounter 16 (1-day, visit_occurrence_id=Enc13, visit_detail_parent_id=Enc14)
-->
